    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm trying to setup neovim using built-in plugin manager available in latest nightly build v0.12.\n\nDocumentation of `vim.pack.add()` shows you can define plugin spec with optional arbitrary data associated with a plugin. I'm using this field to execute build command when plugin in installed.\n\nThis plugin spec is supposed to be passed into `PackChanged` autocmd callback but that is not the case when `nvim-pack-lock.json` file is present on first run.\n\nMy understanding was that with nvim package lockfile, I should be able to recreate my neovim setup with exact version anytime. It doesn't work as expected because what is passed into `PackChanged` autocmd callback depends on presence of `nvim-pack-lock.json` file.\n\nI have listed sample `init.lua` and `nvim-pack-lock.json` that can be used to reproduce this issue.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nInit.lua:\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"PackChanged\", {\n  callback = function(ev)\n    local plugin = ev.data\n\n    print(string.format(\"PackChanged event fired for: %s\", plugin.spec.name))\n    print(string.format(\"Plugin spec: %s\", vim.inspect(plugin.spec)))\n\n    local pch = (plugin.spec.data or {}).pack_changed_hook\n    if type(pch) == \"function\" and (plugin.kind == \"install\" or plugin.kind == \"update\") then\n      pcall(pch, plugin)\n    end\n  end,\n})\n\nvim.pack.add({\n  {\n    src = 'https://github.com/nvim-telescope/telescope-fzf-native.nvim',\n    data = {\n      pack_changed_hook = function(plugin)\n        print(string.format(\"Inside pack_changed_hook for: %s\", plugin.spec.name))\n        vim.system({ 'make' }, { cwd = plugin.path })\n      end,\n    },\n  },\n}, { confirm = false })\n\n```\n\nnvim-pack-lock.json:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"plugins\": {\n    \"telescope-fzf-native.nvim\": {\n      \"rev\": \"6fea601bd2b694c6f2ae08a6c6fab14930c60e2c\",\n      \"src\": \"https://github.com/nvim-telescope/telescope-fzf-native.nvim\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- Make sure neovim environment is clean with no plugins installed. \n- Put these files in neovim config directory.  \n- Start neovim\n- Plugin will be installed but build command is never executed because `data` field is missing inside `PackChanged` autocmd handler.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThis is the output I expected in neovim messages:\n\n```\nPackChanged event fired for: telescope-fzf-native.nvim\nPlugin spec: {\n  data = {\n    pack_changed_hook = <function 1>\n  },\n  name = \"telescope-fzf-native.nvim\",\n  src = \"https://github.com/nvim-telescope/telescope-fzf-native.nvim\"\n}\nInside pack_changed_hook for: telescope-fzf-native.nvim\n```\n\nand a file: `$XDG_DATA_HOME/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/telescope-fzf-native.nvim/build/libfzf.so`\n\nInstead this is the output I get:\n\n```\nPackChanged event fired for: telescope-fzf-native.nvim\nPlugin spec: {\n  name = \"telescope-fzf-native.nvim\",\n  src = \"https://github.com/nvim-telescope/telescope-fzf-native.nvim\"\n}\n```\nAbove shows that `data` field from plugin spec is not passed in. So plugin spec function that runs `make` never get executed.\n\nIf you delete `nvim-pack-lock.json` and try again using clean environment, all of plugin spec is passed into `PackChanged` autocmd callback. Everything works.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0-dev-2459+g62135f5a57\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS Tahoe 26.3\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty v1.2.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nDownloaded latest nighly build from this repo",
