            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Without knowing much internal working and future plan for new fields in `vim.pack.Spec`, my two cents are:\n\n- Usually lock file in package management has specific purpose of locking down version of package to be installed\n- In theory this is how I would assume it works:\n     - `PackChangedPre` and `PackChanged` are supposed to receive plugin specification in `event-data`.spec \n     - whatever fields are specified in `vim.pack.add()` must be passed to event callback\n     - values of those field can come from either lockfile or `vim.pack.add()`\n- When app starts,\n     - it sees lockfile and loads it,\n     - then add in any missing fields from current `vim.pack.add()`\n\nThat way what is fields passed into `PackChangedPre` and `PackChanged` are always consistent wheter it is from first run using lockfile or without lockfile.\n\n",
