            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> * it sees lockfile and loads it,\n> \n> * then add in any missing fields from current `vim.pack.add()`\n\nLockfile data and plugin specification are two different things, so there is nothing to add from the second to the first.\n\nIt is a matter of adjusting which data from `vim.pack.add()` is passed down during lockfile synchronization. So that the possible \"install plugins from lockfile\" step indeed contains user-defined data. I have a reasonable prototype, need time to think this through a bit more.",
